text: Cœur-de-la-Vallée is a commune. It is in Grand Est in the Marne department in northeast France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2023 and consists of the former communes of Reuil (the seat), Binson-et-Orquigny and Villers- sous-Châtillon. == Related pages == * Communes of the Marne department == References == Category:2023 establishments in France Category:Communes in Marne
title: Cœur-de-la-Vallée
